summary: I was hearing David Tennant does a podcast with Olivia Colman and she basically said that she hates "fame" (she didn't say it...
body:
I was hearing David Tennant does a podcast with Olivia Colman and she basically said that she hates “fame” (she didn’t say it like that exactly), she hates being recognised on the street and that people somehow think they own you and they just take pictures on the street of you and all that stuff we know, and she said that the way she deals with that is not going out, like she hangs at her home or at her friend’s home, but she just doesn’t go out anymore.

And then DT said, even if it was just like a passing thought, that it was hard for him too, even if he was in his 30s and that he had to basically talk to someone (I guess a therapist) about it because it messed him up a bit, and then Olivia said she also had to talk to someone about it.

And then they both agreed on how if it was hard for them how difficult it must be for someone who gets that kind of weird (mostly unwanted) attention since they are teenagers…

summary: I absolutely live for David Tennant’s performance in the bookstore, the store around him on fire as he slowly realizes that...
body:
I absolutely live for David Tennant’s performance in the bookstore, the store around him on fire as he slowly realizes that Aziraphale got sent back to heaven.

There are many (many, many, maaany) amazing moments in this show, but this moment was just so good from David. Amazing. I love this man.
